Consider the following program given below:
int demo(int n, int m) {
  if (m < 2) return m;
  if (n < 1) return n;
  else if (n < 10)
    return demo(n/m, m);
  else
    return demo(n - 1, m);
}
What is worst case time complexity of this code in terms of n? (Choose the tightest upper bound)

Consider the following code fragment:
int i = 0;
while(i < 10) {
  printf("%d", i);
  i++; }
Choose the fragments which does not produce the same output?

options.text:
int i = 0;
do {
  printf("%d", i);
  i++; }
while(i < 10);

int i = 0;
while (i < 10) {
  i++; printf("%d", i); }

